
BBC Radio 1
instance
BBC Radio 1 is a British radio station operated by the British Broadcasting Corporation which also broadcasts internationally, specialising in modern and current popular music and chart hits throughout the day. Radio 1 provides alternative genres after 7:00 pm, including electronic dance, hip hop, rock, indie or interviews. It is aimed primarily at the 15â€“29 age group, although the average age of the UK audience in 2008 was 33. BBC Radio 1 started 24 hour broadcasting on 1st May 1991.
